# Project workflow rules

## PRD drift detection
- This project uses a formal PRD at `docs/PRD.md`.
- When you modify an implementation file, remind the user to run `/prd-sync` at session end.
- Never claim a requirement is implemented without a `file:line` reference.
- A test is not an implementation.

## Before solving any non-trivial problem
1. Ask: "Should I search shared memory for prior solutions to this?"
2. If yes, query ArangoDB `shared_patterns` collection via the arangodb-memory-mcp MCP:
   `FOR p IN shared_patterns FILTER CONTAINS(LOWER(p.problem_description), "<keyword>") SORT p.created_at DESC LIMIT 5 RETURN p`

## After solving a reusable problem
- Offer to save the solution to `shared_patterns` via the MCP `upsert-document` tool.

## Session end
- Remind the user to run `/prd-sync` if implementation files changed.
